info.headline: Special Weather Statement issued October 12 at 3:10AM EDT by NWS Jacksonville
info.description: ...A STRONG THUNDERSTORM WILL IMPACT NORTHERN PUTNAM COUNTY THROUGH 345 AM EDT... At 310 AM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm capable of producing a landspout near Hollister, or near Interlachen, moving northeast at 40 mph. HAZARD...Landspouts and wind gusts around 40 mph. SOURCE...Radar indicated. IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible. Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around unsecured objects. Locations impacted include... Palatka, Interlachen, Bostwick, Bardin, Hollister, Carraway, and Mannville. LANDSPOUT...POSSIBLE MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH
info.instruction: If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
